    "extras": [
      "Uber is the easiest app-based ride option in Beirut and for airport transfers, but outside the capital most travelers rely on servees/shared taxis, arranged hotel drivers or a rental car.",
      "Jeita Grotto (~₹7,290), Byblos Castle (~₹4,320), Baalbek (~₹8,100) and the Cedars of God reserve (~₹1,350) are the main paid anchors in this plan; Qadisha Valley hiking itself is generally free.",
      "Intercity vans and service taxis are usually cash-first and often leave only when full, so keep small LBP notes even if your hotel quotes prices in USD.",
      "A rental car becomes most useful for Baalbek, Qadisha and Cedars combinations, where same-day backtracking by public transport can waste hours.",
      "Harissa, Palm Islands boats and some museums can shift prices with the exchange rate, so treat smaller quoted INR amounts as approximate even when the major heritage ticket prices are fixed at the gate in LBP."
    ],
